## 2. Universal Architecture & Component Trees

### 2.1 Backend Pipeline Execution
The operation route implements a multi-stage request filtering process.

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant UI as React Operations UI
    participant Auth as Express Auth Middleware
    participant RBAC as Role Verifier Guard
    participant Logic as Controller Business Rules
    participant DB as MongoDB Atlas

    UI->>Auth: GET /api/orders (JWT in Header)
    Auth-->>Auth: Validate JWT Signature
    Auth->>RBAC: Token Valid. Pass to Role Check.
    RBAC-->>RBAC: Is user 'manager' or 'cashier'?
    RBAC->>Logic: Role authorized. Proceed.
    Logic->>DB: Perform Queries / Aggregations
    DB-->>Logic: Return normalized datasets
    Logic-->>UI: 200 OK (JSON Payload)
```

