## 5. Critical Function & Implementation Specs

### 5.1 Business Logic Enforcement: "Safe Deletion"
A critical business requirement dictates that no active/paid order can be deleted. This protects the integrity of payment traces and session logs.

**Backend Implementation (`/server/routes/orders.js`):**
```javascript
// DELETE /api/orders — Delete draft orders only
router.delete('/', authorize('manager'), async (req, res) => {
  const { ids } = req.body;
  
  // Isolate validation against immutable database state
  const orders = await Order.find({ _id: { $in: ids } });
  const nonDraft = orders.filter((o) => o.status !== 'draft');
  
  // If even ONE non-draft order is passed, the entire chain is rejected.
  if (nonDraft.length > 0) {
    return res.status(400).json({
      success: false,
      message: `Cannot delete ${nonDraft.length} non-draft order(s). Only draft orders can be deleted.`,
    });
  }

  // Safe to physical purge
  await Order.deleteMany({ _id: { $in: ids }, status: 'draft' });
  res.json({ success: true, message: `${ids.length} draft order(s) deleted` });
});
```

### 5.2 MongoDB Aggregation: Payment Grouping
To maintain fluid performance on enormous transaction logs, sorting and mapping is completed via native MongoDB aggregation. This condenses thousands of documents into mere bytes sent to the client.

**Backend Implementation (`/server/routes/payments.js`):**
```javascript
const grouped = await Payment.aggregate([
  {
    $group: {
      _id: '$method', // Creates unique groups for 'cash', 'card', 'upi'
      totalAmount: { $sum: '$amount' }, // Server-side recursive addition
      count: { $sum: 1 },
      payments: {
        $push: { // Array compression
          _id: '$_id',
          amount: '$amount',
          orderNumber: '$orderNumber',
          customerName: '$customerName',
          createdAt: '$createdAt',
        },
      },
    },
  },
  { $sort: { totalAmount: -1 } }, // Push highest grossing method to top
]);
```

### 5.3 UX Engineering: Interactive Floating Multi-Select
A massive usability improvement achieved by pushing actions dynamically when selection logic changes.

**UI State Logic (`OrdersListView.jsx`):**
```javascript
// Multi Select Toggles
const toggleSelect = (id) => {
  setSelected((prev) => prev.includes(id) 
    ? prev.filter((x) => x !== id) 
    : [...prev, id]);
};

const toggleAll = () => {
  setSelected(selected.length === orders.length 
    ? [] : orders.map((o) => o._id));
};

// UI Rendering Condition Pipeline (JSX Context)
{selected.length > 0 && (
  <div className="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4 p-3 bg-white rounded-2xl border border-stone-200 shadow-card animate-slide-down">
     <span className="text-sm font-display font-semibold text-stone-700">
       {selected.length} selected
     </span>
     {/* Condition Inject: Roles */}
     {isManager && (
       <button onClick={handleDelete} className="text-red-600 bg-red-50 border-red-200 hover:bg-red-100">
         Delete Drafts
       </button>
     )}
  </div>
)}
```

